==Abstract==

This IIP specifies the channel management protocol for INTcoin Lightning, adapted from BOLT #2 for ML-DSA-87 signatures.

==Specification==

===Channel States===

<pre>
NONE → INIT_SENT → ACCEPT_RECEIVED → FUNDING_CREATED → FUNDING_SIGNED
    → AWAITING_FUNDING_DEPTH → NORMAL → SHUTDOWN_SENT → CLOSING_NEGOTIATION
    → CLOSED
</pre>

===Opening Protocol===

# Funder sends '''open_channel'''
# Acceptor responds with '''accept_channel'''
# Funder broadcasts funding tx, sends '''funding_created'''
# Acceptor responds with '''funding_signed'''
# Both send '''channel_ready''' after confirmations

===open_channel Fields===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Field !! Description
|-
| chain_hash || Genesis block hash
|-
| funding_mint || Channel capacity
|-
| push_mint || Initial amount to peer
|-
| dust_limit_mint || Minimum output value
|-
| channel_reserve_mint || Required reserve
|-
| to_self_delay || CSV delay for outputs
|-
| funding_pubkey || Funding public key (2592 bytes)
|-
| revocation_basepoint || Revocation key base
|-
| payment_basepoint || Payment key base
|-
| htlc_basepoint || HTLC key base
|-
| first_per_commitment_point || First commitment point
|}

===Commitment Transaction===

# '''Funding Input''': 2-of-2 multisig
# '''To-Local Output''': Our balance with CSV delay
# '''To-Remote Output''': Their balance (immediate)
# '''HTLC Outputs''': One per pending HTLC

To-Local Script:
<pre>
OP_IF
    <revocation_pubkey>
OP_ELSE
    <to_self_delay> OP_CHECKSEQUENCEVERIFY OP_DROP
    <local_delayedpubkey>
OP_ENDIF
OP_CHECKSIG_DILITHIUM
</pre>

===Closing===

====Cooperative Close====

# Either party sends '''shutdown''' with closing script
# Parties negotiate via '''closing_signed'''
# Final closing tx broadcast

====Force Close====

Broadcast latest commitment transaction. Broadcaster's outputs time-locked.

===Breach Remedy===

If counterparty broadcasts revoked commitment:
# Non-broadcaster holds revocation secret
# Can claim ALL channel funds via penalty tx

